Periodic regression sweep

Run this periodically (and after any modernization touch in core estimator paths):

./issue_notes/run_verified_issue_repros.sh

Optional explicit log path:

./issue_notes/run_verified_issue_repros.sh /tmp/nprmpi_issue_notes_repros_manual.log

Pass/fail rule:

- any `FAIL:` line in the run log is a regression candidate and blocks merge until triaged.

Route validation sweep (manual-broadcast + attach + profile)

Run this after MPI routing/runtime changes (or before declaring 4-path pass-muster):

./issue_notes/run_attach_profile_validations.sh

Optional explicit output directory:

./issue_notes/run_attach_profile_validations.sh /Users/jracine/Development/tmp_ll_lc_lp_alignment/nprmpi_route_validation_manual

Scripts used by the runner:

- `issue_notes/validate_route_manual_broadcast.R`
- `issue_notes/validate_route_attach.R`
- `issue_notes/validate_route_profile.R`
- `issue_notes/validate_route_profile_plot.R`

Current status (2026-03-02):

- manual-broadcast route passes in current tree.
- attach route passes in current tree.
- profile route passes in current tree when launched with the documented profile contract:
  `R_PROFILE_USER=<.../Rprofile>`, `R_PROFILE=""`, and `R CMD BATCH --no-save` (no `--vanilla`).
- profile-plot route passes in current tree for direct master `plot(...)` with
  `npRmpi.autodispatch=TRUE`, and nested `mpi.bcast.cmd(plot(...))` fails fast by contract.

Plot operational gate (migrated plot methods)

Run this to validate migrated plot-method operability in one pass:

./issue_notes/run_plot_operational_gate.sh

Optional explicit output directory:

./issue_notes/run_plot_operational_gate.sh /tmp/nprmpi_plot_operational_gate_manual

What it runs:

- session/attach tiny plot sanity smokes,
- plot-focused contract suite (helper/bootstrap/guardrails/session subprocess),
- attach/profile/profile-plot route matrix via `run_attach_profile_validations.sh`,
- orphan slave-process scan and summarized pass/fail report.
